 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=klumhru>Klumhru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/30/01 1:02:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grouping specs</span><hr size=1> I now have some 240 spectre kills to my name, and I'd like to share some points. I'm 48 now and plan to try to use these guys to 51 (Column of Frost, Wyvern time), but I've seen some trying to use the tactic I used originally. At first I tried pulling them down to the shore and then kiting them along the shore line. I did find out though that I often had them in awkward positions, either high above me, or far below. So I decided to experiment with pulling them along on top of the Island, and have found that this works much better. There are several points that jut out from the &quot;hat&quot; of the Island, so to speak, and allow you a long view over a relatively flat area. I found that running between these points counterclockwise allowed me to get to each point exactly when CoF popped, nuke, run to next, etc. I've even started referring to these points as nuking stations :-) Lev and SoW/JBoots required of course.<br>
Also some stats:<br>
11 minutes per quad (approx at L47, can range from 10-12)<br>
3 quads per SoW potion charge<br>
1 - 1.2 blue bub of xp per quad<br>
1 yellow per hour<br>
1 Level per 5 hours<br>
